<TITLE> Ban Ki-moon expresses deep shock at loss of lives </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 13 (bdnews24.com) -- The United Nations secretary-general Tuesday expressed deep sadness at the devastation and loss of more than 100 lives in the port city of Chittagong, a statement has said. Torrents of rain triggered collapse of hills in the city, leaving at least 118 people dead and scores injured. The death toll stood at 118 Wednesday while rescuers continued to search for more bodies in the battered city. Ban Ki-moon extends his deepest condolences to the families of those who have been killed or injured in the disaster, his spokesperson said in the statement. He said that the UN "stands ready to assist as required". Meanwhile, the United Nations' development agency has allocated $20,000 (Tk 13.66 lakh) to add to the national effort to cope with the landslide emergency in Chittgaong. The United Nations Development Programme in a statement said it had dispatched five vehicles, fuel and drivers to the scene to support rescue and relief operations. A medical team has been kept on standby to support the government, UNDP said. bd
